  "title": "Youth Worker |School |Lor Ah  Soo",
  "description": "<p><strong>The Services required are set out as follows:</strong></p><p>1. To interact with identified students on a regular basis over</p><p>a prolonged duration (approximately 10 months) and provide</p><p>positive mentoring and counselling support for students.</p><p>2. To connect with identified students, build positive</p><p>relationships and contribute to the holistic development of the</p><p>students.</p><p>3. To plan and conduct intervention programmes, including</p><p>house visits where necessary, customised to students’ needs</p><p>and aligned to the school’s efforts in character development.</p><p>4. To observe and identify some of the key needs of the</p><p>students and to report such cases to the Student Management</p><p>Key Personnel and/ or School Leaders for further intervention</p><p>and support.</p><p>5. To attend case review/ case management meetings with</p><p>relevant school personnel to provide feedback on students’</p><p>needs, programme experience and concerns, so that the</p><p>school can better support the students.</p><p>6. To conduct themselves professionally in their interactions</p><p>with the students and school personnel, and work with the</p><p>Student Management and Student Development teams in</p><p>supporting the students.</p><p>7. To practise the areas of responsibilities and behaviour</p><p>during all of his or her school engagements as listed in</p><p>Annex C – Expectations of Instructor</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
